<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="123" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                    <head>No. 119.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beach</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard.</persName></hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guayaquil</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-07-30"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30, 1885</date>.
                            (Received July 30.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Santos’s cousin here. Received letter yesterday from relative saying Santos
                        released twenty-second (22d). Think statement reliable.</p>
                    <closer><signed>BEACH.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>